[2] Cholera - Sudan (South)
Date: Tue, 28 Mar 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Medair [edited]
<http://www.reliefweb.int/rw/RWB.NSF/db900SID/EKOI-6NC57A?OpenDocument>

The cholera outbreak in South Sudan has come under control in the 2 most
affected areas of Yei and Juba. However, there continue to be new reported
cases in various towns and villages. WHO reports that up to 20 Mar 2006 a
total of 8923 cases and 238 deaths had been reported for the whole of
southern Sudan.
